## `fs.readFileSync`

Synchronous methods block the thread until the operation completes. They're simpler but can hurt performance in servers.

```javascript
const fs = require('fs');

try {
  const data = fs.readFileSync('example.txt', 'utf8');
  console.log('File content:', data);
} catch (err) {
  console.error('Error:', err);
}
```

Use synchronous versions mainly in startup code or scripts, not in request handlers.
